			<!-- Begin News/Information Section -->
				<table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" ID="Table23">
					<tr id="trmasthead">
						<td valign="middle" class="main_font" align="center">
							<font size="3"><b>&nbsp;</b></font>
					    </td>
					</tr>
					
					   <td>

			
			
			



<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Magical Kicks and Punches</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=409044" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    Absor <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/everquest/Forum1/HTML/000065.html">explained</a> why some classes cannot use magical attacks via kicking or punching:
<blockquote>
<i><p>
I was fighting willowisps a couple months ago to get some extra cash and another light stone. I had noticed that throughout my fighting career that the boots I wore determined if I could hit ghouls, wisps, etc with kicks. Regular bronze boots yielded the INVULNERABLE message, while my crafted boots, because they were magic, yielding connecting hits that caused damage. On the flip side later I wanted to work with my hand to hand skill since I am supposed to be a fighting machine as a warrior. I had on crafted gloves that were classified as magic, yet everything such as ghouls and wisps that I tried to fight gave me the INVULNERABLE message when I tried to punch. If kick is a secondary skill but allows us to cause dmg to mobs if magic boots are worn, why is a primary fighting skill like hand to hand not able to share the same effect? I haven't tried this in a couple of months because I haven't seen anything in the patch message to tell me that this issue has been addressed!</p></i>
<b><p>
You're correct. Initially, fists were never hurting creatures that required magic weapons to damage. Special coding was added to allow Monks to cause damage to such creatures with magical gloves. It was not given to other classes because it is a special code for Monks.</p>
<p>
Obviously the same thing could have been done with kicking as well, only allowing Monks to kick for damage with magic boots against resistant creatures. But Warriors use kick quite a bit, and so it was decided to let them kick for damage under those circumstances. Or it could have gone the other way. It could have been, as you suggested, that everyone with magic gloves could punch resistant creatures.</p>
<p>
Either of those choices would have been more consistent, I suppose. But it's just a perk for Monks, really. It can easily be explained in game by the fact that Monks are skilled in the use of all their limbs as weapons and that's how they can use magical armor as a weapon. The Warrior only knows how to do so through practice with kicking and that he hasn't the skill with his fists to do so (and you'll find that it's probably true that few Warriors have much skill with Hand to Hand)</p>
<p>
Alan</p></b>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
		     <td valign="top">
